article.headline: Incarnate Word defeats UAPB 92-64
article.description: — Dylan Hayman scored 18 points as Incarnate Word beat Arkansas-Pine Bluff 92-64 on Saturday night.
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- — Dylan Hayman scored 18 points as Incarnate Word beat Arkansas-Pine Bluff 92-64 on Saturday night. Hayman added seven rebounds and five assists for the Cardinals (3-1). Jordan Pyke scored 17 points and added eight rebounds, six assists, and three steals. Davion Bailey shot 6 for 13 (3 for 10 from 3-point range) and 2 of 3 from the free-throw line to finish with 17 points. Klemen Vuga led the way for the Golden Lions (1-4) with 19 points and six rebounds. Christian Moore added 15 points and five assists for UAPB. Raphael Dumont also put up nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
